{
  "texts": [
    "Across both the ComVE and CSE datasets, the TIP framework consistently outperformed the RK approach in all metrics, of model size.Specifically, in the results of the ComVE dataset (Table 4a), with the Llama 2 70B as both the explanation generator and the knowledge generator, TIP achieved a BLEU score of 0.0175 compared to RK's 0.0125 and a SentBERT score of 0.6850 compared to RK's 0.5829, indicating improved fluency and stronger semantic alignment in the generated explanations.",
    "These results demonstrate that TIP's targeted nonsensical concept identification and precise implicit knowledge generation yield more accurate and contextually appropriate explanations.",
    "In the results of the CSE dataset (Table 4b), TIP also achieved a significantly higher performance compared to RK.",
    "Furthermore, the performance gap becomes more pronounced with larger models.These findings underscore the necessity of identifying nonsensical concepts prior to implicit knowledge generation.",
    "The nonsensical concepts provide crucial context, enabling the knowledge generator to produce more relevant implicit knowledge."
  ]
}